The complete text of the GNU General Public Licenses are available in GPLv2.txt
(version 2) and GPLv3.txt (version 3). They define the license terms of many 
components within this distribution, but not the distribution as a whole.

A README.BETA file is present and effective while the product is in 
preproduction phase.

#############################################################
Sources for development releases are not distributed by mirrors to
reduce the bandwidth and storage on these mirrors.

For full information on how to get the source code, please read:
http://en.opensuse.org/Source_code

The latest source for the development tree is available from:
http://download.opensuse.org/tumbleweed/repo/src-oss/ and 
http://download.opensuse.org/tumbleweed/repo/src-non-oss/

The latest source for releases is available from:
http://download.opensuse.org/source/distribution/

If you like to request the source for a specific release of openSUSE
on DVD, send an e-mail to:
	sourcedvd@opensuse.org 

or write to:
	SUSE Software Solutions Germany GmbH
	openSUSE Team
	Frankenstra√üe 146
	D-90461 Nuernberg
	Germany

Please note that we charge $15 or 15 Euros to cover our costs of
distribution.
